pan.js adds native-like panning functionality
for any element that is bigger than itâ€™s container
for iPad and iPhone and desktop browsers.

Download the demo and try it out.

Browser support: IE7+, FF3+, Opera 10+, Chrome, Safari, iPad and iPhone (and probably more devices as well).

--

Usage:
  Pan( HTMLElement ); // adds panning for the element

--

Methods:
There is just one method exposed for destroying the pan:
  var pan = new Pan( HTMLElment );
  pan.destroy(); // removes all events